                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
                    <tr>
                      <td><font size="3">Tokelau</font></td>
                      <td align="right"> <font size="3"><img src="../../img/flags/flg_tokelau.gif" width="70" height="35"></font></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" height="1">
                    <tr background="../../img/maps/cp_tile.gif" valign="top"> 
                      <td background="../../img/maps/cp_tile.gif"><img src="../../img/maps/cp_space.gif" width="37" height="1"></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                  <p class="profile_intro">Tokelau is a largely self-governing 
                    territory under the administration of New Zealand. Its inhabitants 
                    are citizens of New Zealand. Despite outside pressures, the 
                    Faka Tokelau (the traditional Tokelauan family and community-oriented 
                    way of life) has remained very strong. 
                  <p align="center"><img src="../../img/maps/cp_tokalau.gif" width="480" height="312" alt="Map of Tokelau"></p>
                  <br>
                  <h5><a name="facts"></a>Facts and Figures</h5>
